In ROS 2, “launch files”  are special files used to start and manage multiple nodes at once.


🚀 What is a launch file?

A launch file is like a startup script for your robot system.

Instead of running many commands one by one, you write one launch file that:

- Starts multiple nodes
- Sets parameters
- Connects everything together


🧠 Simple idea

Without launch file:
run node1
run node2
run node3

With launch file:
run everything using 1 command ✅

📂 Types of launch files in ROS 2
ROS 2 mainly uses Python-based launch files:
.launch.py ✅ (most common)
XML format (older style, less used)

▶️ How to run a launch file
Use this command:
ros2 launch <package_name> <file_name.launch.py>

Example:
ros2 launch my_package my_launch_file.launch.py


🔧 What can launch files do?
They can:
- Start multiple nodes at once
- Set parameters (like speed, topic names)
- Remap topics
- Launch nodes on different machines
- Add delays or conditions

create launch folder in package section 
ros2_ws
